
[1]atrocious

   ATRO'CIOUS, a. [L. atrox, trux, fierce, cruel.]

   1. Extremely hainous, criminal or cruel; enormous; outrageous; as
   atrocious guilt or offense.

   2. Very grievous; violent; as atrocious distempers.
